WEBVTT

00:00.994 --> 00:02.216
All right, good morning everybody.

00:02.256 --> 00:03.858
Nice to see you all.

00:04.559 --> 00:06.903
Why don't you join with me as we just pray to start.

00:08.125 --> 00:10.749
So Father God, I'll be listening this time to you.

00:10.929 --> 00:15.156
We'll thank you that we can come together to learn more about you, to learn more about your word, Lord.

00:15.196 --> 00:23.589
I pray that what we look at today wouldn't just be in our heads, that it would fall down to our hearts, Lord, that you would connect with each one of us afresh this morning.

00:24.250 --> 00:27.154
Lord, anything that is of you, let that remain,

00:27.362 --> 00:29.055
Anything that's not for you, that they'll just be lost.

00:29.417 --> 00:30.566
I'm blown away by the wind.

00:30.828 --> 00:31.896
In Jesus' name.

00:31.956 --> 00:32.178
Amen.

00:34.242 --> 00:49.999
Right, so, as you will hopefully know, most of you will know, we have been looking at this theme of pray the Jesus way since about September, and we're looking at the Lord's prayer, and there's that wonderful thing that we've been working it through line by line, and you know each line as it's gonna come, right?

00:50.540 --> 01:03.474
And when it was announced, I kind of going through them and thinking, oh, okay, lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil, that's gonna be, that's gonna be a toughy, that's gonna be fun, I can't wait to hear what, Wendy or Pete or Nikki or Matt,

01:03.554 --> 01:06.258
has to say on that, that'll be great, wouldn't it?

01:06.278 --> 01:08.621
So I'd like to introduce now.

01:11.064 --> 01:14.189
But yeah, because God has a sense of humour, here we are.

01:15.370 --> 01:18.354
But so I'm going to start today with a question.

01:18.454 --> 01:19.476
And my question is this.

01:20.237 --> 01:26.245
Have you ever met somebody, one of those people, who cannot accept something just because they're told it?

01:26.325 --> 01:28.328
They have to try it for themselves.

01:28.548 --> 01:32.754
There's one great hand at the back here, just waving wildly, I love that.

01:32.994 --> 01:38.201
Yeah, it's that thing that you see the wet paint sign and you have to touch it to check that it's wet.

01:38.682 --> 01:41.385
Or they deliver the food at the restaurant and they say, mind out, the plate is hot.

01:41.666 --> 01:45.050
And you go, and you have to touch the plate and go, oh, that's a hot plate.

01:46.092 --> 01:50.698
People who, whenever you see a button that says, do not press, just have to press it.

01:52.120 --> 01:53.301
Well, I'm one of those people.

01:54.623 --> 01:56.005
And I know it's so annoying.

01:56.025 --> 01:57.807
I'm told by the people who love me that it's so annoying.

01:57.827 --> 01:58.829
But I am one of those people.

01:58.889 --> 02:00.812
And I inherited it from my dad.

02:00.912 --> 02:02.674
I'm going to tell you this little story.

02:02.754 --> 02:20.583
We went to Turkey when I was about six years old and this wasn't like fancy turkey teeth glam beaches kind of Turkey this was cold wet mountainous Turkey in an area called capidocia and So yeah, I was about six years old and here's a couple of great little photos just for reference.

02:20.603 --> 02:24.850
There we go might bring that haircut back and

02:25.442 --> 02:35.155
Anyway, so we're driving through, you can see it's quite a mountain stair, it's all very snowy, driving down this road that hasn't had any traffic along it for probably a few hours, haven't seen any cars anywhere at all.

02:35.836 --> 02:45.810
My dad wants to pull over by the side of the road to take a photo, and we've got the people that we've gone to visit travelling with us in the car, and they say, oh, don't pull over to the side, you'll get stuck.

02:46.498 --> 02:54.566
Now, you think that if the people who are native to that country are saying this to you, that you might follow through with that, but he obviously felt the need to find this out for himself.

02:54.586 --> 02:59.391
He pulls over to the side of the road and we go, and what?

02:59.431 --> 02:59.992
Yeah, I know, right?

03:00.012 --> 03:01.113
The great gasp.

03:01.133 --> 03:14.066
And the snow, and the beautiful kind of snow cover thing, actually, there is a massive ditch that we're into by about two foot in the side of the cart, and there is absolutely no way that we are getting out.

03:14.754 --> 03:19.340
I mean, I was about six years old at this point, so I don't remember being especially concerned.

03:19.661 --> 03:27.752
I remember we had one Mars bar between us as a family in the car, which I promptly ate, and I spent most of my time throwing snowballs, and I wasn't particularly concerned.

03:28.073 --> 03:30.957
But it was quite a concerning situation that we were in.

03:30.997 --> 03:32.439
We were stranded in the middle of nowhere.

03:32.939 --> 03:36.605
Mobile phones weren't a thing at this time, and to be honest, even if they were, I don't know who we would have called.

03:36.945 --> 03:40.530
Hadn't seen any traffic gone through for several hours, and actually

03:40.738 --> 03:45.403
it started to get a bit hairy and I think the adults in the group started to panic.

03:46.384 --> 03:48.507
And it must have been about four hours that we were there.

03:48.527 --> 03:51.590
You know the point where you start to just get really cold.

03:51.830 --> 03:55.374
Like we're actually, all cold just sets in, doesn't matter what you've got with you.

03:56.095 --> 03:57.536
So let's get really, really cold.

03:57.576 --> 04:06.386
And then a car came past, thank goodness, and a winch and a set of snow chains later and we were out and on the way and thankfully all was well.

04:07.027 --> 04:09.970
And apart from the opportunity to show off

04:10.146 --> 04:11.168
That great haircut.

04:11.488 --> 04:13.771
Why am I telling you all of this?

04:14.733 --> 04:24.287
Well, if my dad had listened to some guidance in the first place, if he had trusted the wisdom of what he was being told, then we'd all have been shared from this very shivery experience.

04:24.928 --> 04:39.570
And in the same vein, if I could trust that the plate was hot or that the wall was wet, if I could trust what I was being told, rather than having to find it all out for my own good, then maybe I'd have been spared some painty hands and some burned fingers.

04:40.706 --> 04:50.035
Because when we doubt God, and when we doubt His leading and His goodness and His plans for us, it's all too easy to head off in our own direction and end up in a ditch.

04:51.096 --> 04:57.503
So here we are talking about lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil.

04:59.345 --> 05:04.650
See, I think at least for me, I need God to guide me away from my temptations and my bad decisions.

05:05.391 --> 05:08.914
And when I inevitably don't listen and I decide that I want to go my own way,

05:09.186 --> 05:11.649
Thankfully, he is there to winch me out again.

05:12.490 --> 05:21.381
And it's funny, because I've actually spoken to a number of people about this message from the last couple of weeks, and I've told them that I'm preaching on this, and everyone's having the same reaction where they've gone, oh, I'm really excited to hear that.

05:21.682 --> 05:23.885
Please don't point at me and use me as an example.

05:25.847 --> 05:32.876
Because you might not be one of those people that has to touch the wet pain or the hot plate, but temptation is something that is universal.

05:34.238 --> 05:37.682
And the problem is that most of the time, we know the difference between right and wrong.

05:38.050 --> 05:40.454
We know what's tempting us, and we know to stay away from it.

05:41.075 --> 05:42.357
But it's just so enticing.

05:42.737 --> 05:43.739
We just can't help it.

05:44.340 --> 05:48.566
And Paul, I think Paul sums it up really well in Romans 7 when he says this.

05:48.747 --> 05:51.030
He says, I do not understand what I do.

05:51.671 --> 05:53.414
For what I want to do, I do not do.

05:53.995 --> 05:55.257
But what I hate, I do.

05:55.297 --> 05:59.503
For I have the desire to do what is good, but I cannot carry it out.

06:00.144 --> 06:02.528
For I do not do the good thing I want to do.

06:03.209 --> 06:06.354
But the evil I do not want to do, this I keep on doing.

06:08.162 --> 06:12.770
And I think this is one of those things that we're never gonna totally nail this side of eternity.

06:13.431 --> 06:22.406
But if the Lord's Prayer is a blueprint for how we pray, then I think this last time is this blueprint for how we deal with temptation and when we inevitably get it wrong.

06:23.047 --> 06:28.876
And so I wanna break it down into three sections for us this morning and then just have three questions that I'd really like us to take away.

06:29.878 --> 06:34.706
Because, to begin with, I'd say it's a bit confusing because it's the wrong way round.

06:35.202 --> 06:37.145
lead us not into temptation.

06:37.285 --> 06:40.970
It's got the negative in the middle, and we don't really talk like that anymore.

06:41.310 --> 06:45.616
I don't say take not the A12 this morning due to traffic.

06:46.497 --> 06:47.759
It doesn't sound quite right.

06:47.779 --> 06:49.481
I mean, we've been doing some decorating recently.

06:49.521 --> 06:54.128
If I woke up to Amy and I said, send me not to be in queue anymore, for I am weary.

06:55.509 --> 06:58.213
She's going to look at me like I'm even weirder than usual.

07:00.636 --> 07:04.882
But so if I were writing it, I'd probably say, please don't lead me into temptation, God.

07:04.994 --> 07:06.577
or don't let me be tempted.

07:07.519 --> 07:12.049
And the meaning would probably be the same, but the active emphasis would be changed.

07:13.532 --> 07:21.288
And I think that order is really helpful in approaching the rest of this verse with the intended posture, which is where the first thing that we say is lead us.

07:22.531 --> 07:24.114
Now, many of you, I'm sure, will have

07:24.258 --> 07:41.426
had a dog or have a dog and obviously they come with certain things dogs need and they need to be walked and one thing or another and you've probably seen people they take their dog for a walk and it's primarily for the dog's benefit right like that's why you're walking your dog and about two thirds of the way around the walk the dog decides they aren't going any further

07:41.506 --> 07:44.290
And they just kind of starfish on the pavement a little bit like this.

07:44.450 --> 07:47.534
Anybody who has a dog, I feel like, has probably experienced this.

07:47.915 --> 07:48.736
And you see people there.

07:48.756 --> 07:50.378
If you don't have a dog yourself, you see people there.

07:50.598 --> 07:52.080
And they try and coax the dog.

07:52.501 --> 07:53.863
And then they try and encourage the dog.

07:53.883 --> 07:55.665
And then they kind of just gently pull on it.

07:55.705 --> 07:58.269
And before you know it, you're dragging the dog along the pavement.

07:58.990 --> 08:00.372
And that's not really where you want to be.

08:00.832 --> 08:06.400
And so eventually what they do is they give up, they pick the dog up, and they continue walking.

08:07.141 --> 08:07.922
At which point,

08:08.066 --> 08:16.255
you're not walking your dog, you're just acting like a tour bus and giving your dog a guided tour of your local area and it becomes completely pointless.

08:17.136 --> 08:22.923
But my point is this, is you can't lead something that doesn't want to be led.

08:23.603 --> 08:27.428
God doesn't carry us or drag us not into temptation.

08:27.908 --> 08:30.051
He leads us, not into temptation.

08:30.812 --> 08:33.955
But he can only do that if we allow ourselves to be led.

08:35.717 --> 08:36.498
Lead us God.

08:36.994 --> 08:38.656
lead us not into temptation.

08:39.576 --> 08:41.058
Because it sets right from the off.

08:41.098 --> 08:45.462
Our stance and our posture is one that should allow God to lead us.

08:46.643 --> 08:54.230
If we're called to be His disciples, that is, if we're called to be people who follow Jesus, then we need to be willing to allow Him to lead us.

08:54.591 --> 08:58.314
Otherwise, we're just going to be wandering off into trouble.

08:58.334 --> 09:01.057
I can't just say, God, I'm going to go in my own way.

09:01.638 --> 09:04.140
I'm going to deliberately wander towards temptation.

09:04.200 --> 09:04.680
But lead me.

09:04.700 --> 09:06.322
Don't let me fall into temptation.

09:06.786 --> 09:08.007
It doesn't work that way.

09:09.108 --> 09:13.312
And again, if I was going to write this prayer in my ignorance, I probably would have written it differently.

09:13.973 --> 09:16.996
It would make, I would have written it as God, give me more willpower.

09:17.416 --> 09:19.839
Give me the strength to resist temptation.

09:20.479 --> 09:24.243
God, help me be stronger and to make better decisions.

09:25.504 --> 09:28.968
But then I think I'd be missing the point of what this verse is trying to bring out in me.

09:30.389 --> 09:35.314
Because where everything within me wants to say God, give me more control.

09:35.970 --> 09:42.440
Jesus teaches us that avoiding temptation is about taking a posture that says, God, you take more control.

09:45.044 --> 09:49.811
Because I think in my mind's eye, I've been imagining temptation as something kind of like two paths.

09:49.831 --> 09:51.654
It's like a this way or that way.

09:51.674 --> 09:56.301
One is the path of temptation and the other is kind of temptation-free path.

09:56.782 --> 09:59.887
And I've somehow been asking God to help me choose the right path.

10:01.149 --> 10:01.810
But that's not

10:01.922 --> 10:03.865
what leading looks like.

10:04.145 --> 10:06.869
That's more like directing or, I don't know, orienteering.

10:07.510 --> 10:09.913
And that's not what life looks like either.

10:09.973 --> 10:16.182
I'm sure everybody in this room can attest to the fact that it doesn't matter how good you are, how long you have been a Christian for.

10:16.242 --> 10:19.607
Temptation is there, whatever path we choose.

10:20.047 --> 10:21.910
There is no way around it.

10:22.431 --> 10:25.335
Every road has temptation and traps and pitfalls.

10:26.076 --> 10:30.482
And so rather than be our map showing us the temptation for a road to take,

10:30.978 --> 10:36.485
Jesus is the shepherd who leads us safely down the road without falling into temptation's traps.

10:37.827 --> 10:41.472
And it's that Psalm 23 posture that says, the Lord is my shepherd.

10:41.972 --> 10:42.833
I lack nothing.

10:43.574 --> 10:45.477
He makes me lie down in green pastures.

10:46.218 --> 10:48.120
He leads me beside quiet waters.

10:48.681 --> 10:49.883
He refreshes my soul.

10:50.764 --> 10:53.347
He guides me along the right paths for his namesake.

10:54.008 --> 10:58.674
And even though I walk through the darkest valley, I will fear no evil for you are with me.

11:00.162 --> 11:05.787
And it's been spoken from here before, and Pete did a really good message a little while back on sheep.

11:06.328 --> 11:10.332
And the idea that the biblical shepherd is not like modern shepherds as we think of it.

11:10.372 --> 11:15.777
So we're not Clarkson's farm, it's not kind of quad bikes and sheep dogs, and sitting in the back and chasing them to sheep forwards.

11:16.557 --> 11:19.380
But the biblical shepherd is one that leads from the front.

11:20.021 --> 11:24.865
The sheep follow the shepherd's footsteps, because they know that he leads and guides them to safety.

11:25.706 --> 11:29.810
And there's nothing that drives the sheep forward except the trust to follow the shepherd.

11:30.018 --> 11:32.221
and his footsteps and his voice.

11:33.703 --> 11:39.830
Because, Church, we don't have a hope of avoiding temptation if we aren't first able to learn to follow the shepherd.

11:41.332 --> 11:45.257
And that means taking time to listen, to learn, to hear his voice.

11:46.298 --> 11:58.834
It means, as I'm sure many of us have done in the past, I definitely have, not just deciding a direction and then asking God to bless it and to rub a stamp it, but really seeking his will for our life and the choices.

11:59.842 --> 12:06.611
Sometimes it means slowing down and walking behind him when everything in us wants to run ahead.

12:07.212 --> 12:08.033
Have you ever felt like that?

12:09.615 --> 12:10.937
And I get it.

12:11.037 --> 12:14.081
Life is busy and we have things that we want to do.

12:14.642 --> 12:20.069
And if I know that I need to get somewhere and there's an endpoint, then I want to get there as quickly as possible so that I can get onto the new thing.

12:20.089 --> 12:20.710
I don't want to be led.

12:20.730 --> 12:22.332
I don't want to move at God's pace.

12:22.733 --> 12:25.436
I want to move at my pace and the pace that I feel like I'm ready for.

12:27.198 --> 12:29.842
But maybe God is asking us to slow down this morning.

12:30.402 --> 12:38.856
and to follow him so that he can lead us there safely in his timing and not fall into every single ditch along the way.

12:40.659 --> 12:45.187
Because sometimes the ditches themselves aren't the issue.

12:45.768 --> 12:49.033
It's just that I won't allow myself to be led around them.

12:50.075 --> 12:56.786
I don't want my need for control to cause me to end up in a ditch because I want to be someone who allows Jesus to lead me.

12:57.922 --> 13:02.306
And we know, this is the thing we know, and I love this about Jesus, that he gets it.

13:02.406 --> 13:04.448
He gets what we're going through.

13:04.529 --> 13:07.531
He gets that we're going through temptation because he lived it, right?

13:07.552 --> 13:14.058
And we read in Matthew 4, Jesus was led by the spirit into the wilderness to be tempted by the devil.

13:14.098 --> 13:18.322
And that was right before basically one chapter before he praised this prayer with his disciples.

13:19.483 --> 13:19.984
He was led.

13:20.765 --> 13:21.405
He was tempted.

13:22.006 --> 13:23.888
And he overcame temptation.

13:23.928 --> 13:26.290
And ultimately, he overcame sin and death.

13:27.138 --> 13:32.564
And church, if someone's going to lead me somewhere, I want to know that they've walked that before me, right?

13:32.584 --> 13:34.465
I want to know that they've walked that road themselves.

13:35.527 --> 13:41.112
Well, Jesus has walked the road of temptation and Jesus has the authority to lead us through it.

13:41.633 --> 13:50.282
And we can trust him to lead us through it, not just because he's God and he knows everything, but because he's actually walked it before we did.

13:51.343 --> 13:54.706
So can we allow ourselves to be led by him this morning?

13:57.090 --> 13:57.771
But let's say we can.

13:58.531 --> 13:59.192
Let's say, you know what?

13:59.552 --> 14:00.593
Jesus, you are leading us.

14:01.474 --> 14:03.296
Where are we being led in this verse?

14:04.377 --> 14:07.179
Lead us not into temptation.

14:08.841 --> 14:14.266
Because the implication there sounds like God might lead us into temptation, right?

14:14.326 --> 14:15.327
Unless we ask Him to.

14:15.367 --> 14:18.270
If I have to pray, God don't lead me into temptation.

14:18.690 --> 14:20.652
Does that mean that He might lead me into temptation?

14:20.692 --> 14:21.533
If I don't pray that.

14:22.474 --> 14:26.117
And the Bible, thankfully, is very clear that God does not tempt us.

14:26.417 --> 14:27.058
He's not.

14:27.170 --> 14:29.533
leading us into temptations we think might think of it.

14:29.553 --> 14:30.995
He doesn't try and trick us.

14:31.035 --> 14:33.137
He doesn't try and entice us into sin.

14:33.177 --> 14:40.226
And with this verse from James 1 that says, verse 13, it says, When tempted, no one should say God is tempting me.

14:40.847 --> 14:44.110
For God cannot be tempted by evil, nor does he tempt anyone.

14:44.811 --> 14:49.817
But each person is tempted when they are dragged away by their own evil desire and enticed.

14:50.658 --> 14:53.342
Then after desire has conceived, it gives birth to sin.

14:53.862 --> 14:56.946
And sin, when full grown, gives birth to death.

14:58.818 --> 15:04.848
OK, but if God doesn't tempt us, surely he wouldn't lead us into temptation either.

15:05.769 --> 15:08.353
So how do we square these two verses with one another?

15:08.373 --> 15:12.099
Because it seems like Jesus and James contradicting each other in what they say.

15:13.401 --> 15:17.387
Well, the word that's used here for temptation has two meanings.

15:17.488 --> 15:19.611
And it's this, I'm going to butcher the pronunciation.

15:20.032 --> 15:21.614
You can read it.

15:21.674 --> 15:22.776
Perasmos, let's go with that.

15:24.078 --> 15:26.642
Can mean temptation as we now think

15:26.722 --> 15:33.010
So it's this kind of encouragement or enticement into sin, but also it can mean testing.

15:33.771 --> 15:45.565
Testing in a positive sense, something that refines, something that encourages growth and produces loyalty and the situation of pressure where our faithfulness is revealed.

15:46.687 --> 15:53.976
And we said it just a few moments ago in chapter four that Jesus was led by the spirit into the desert to be tempted by the devil.

15:54.897 --> 15:55.858
The spirit led

15:56.386 --> 15:57.648
and the devil tempted.

15:59.932 --> 16:07.545
God tests us in order to refine us, in order for us to grow in our faith and in our faithfulness.

16:08.808 --> 16:14.938
But Satan tempts us, not for our good, but so that we might fall away from God.

16:16.661 --> 16:21.810
And whilst it might not feel like it a lot of the time, we are told that testing is a good

16:21.890 --> 16:27.857
So James 1 says, consider it pure joy in my brothers and sisters whenever you face trials of many kinds.

16:28.517 --> 16:31.661
Because you know that testing of your faith produces perseverance.

16:33.803 --> 16:37.007
But within testing, we want to take shortcuts.

16:37.467 --> 16:39.970
We can be susceptible to take the easy way out, right?

16:40.591 --> 16:41.672
And to fall into sin.

16:41.732 --> 16:45.756
And if you're feeling like this is a slightly odd concept, you're not alone.

16:45.897 --> 16:47.839
And I feel like this as well is kind of testing from God.

16:47.859 --> 16:50.802
So I find it helpful to imagine it like this.

16:51.746 --> 16:55.310
Most people here will have taken an exam at some point.

16:56.351 --> 17:04.201
And whilst we may not like them, and I'm sure most of us here wouldn't choose to take exams unless we had to, they do unfortunately serve an important purpose.

17:04.862 --> 17:09.047
Because nothing really forces you to learn quite like the pressure of an exam.

17:09.888 --> 17:18.738
Maybe some of you are really good at exams, maybe you're really good at being prepared, any of those kind of people, you have your revision timetable as it's all planned out months in advance and all that stuff.

17:18.850 --> 17:33.532
I was a Kramer, for exams, and I always have been, unfortunately, staying up until three o'clock in the morning, trying to force as much knowledge into my head as possible ahead of whatever exam it is the next day, and then it just goes as soon as you're done with it.

17:33.552 --> 17:36.136
A few people nodding in agreement.

17:37.157 --> 17:41.443
But regardless, regardless of how we deal with them, exams are a powerful motivator to learn.

17:41.884 --> 17:48.594
And passing an exam comes with some kind of positive, whether it's a reinforcing of knowledge, or a skill, or a qualification,

17:48.706 --> 17:55.335
And whilst it might not feel particularly fun or enjoyable in the moment, ultimately it is something that is for a purpose.

17:56.676 --> 18:04.587
But with the pressure of an exam comes the fear of failing and the burning desire and the temptation to cheat.

18:05.708 --> 18:09.693
And if you've ever taken an exam, I'm sure you have felt that temptation at some point.

18:10.374 --> 18:16.562
To cut corners, to make it a little bit easier and just to stack the deck so it works in your favour.

18:17.250 --> 18:31.602
to copy off the person next to you or to write answers in the gaps between your fingers, to roll up some paper and put it inside your tie so you can kind of just slip it out for the exam or scratch it on the back of your calculator with a compass if anyone has ever done that.

18:35.586 --> 18:36.667
some shocked faces.

18:37.028 --> 18:40.432
I've never did any of these things when I was at school.

18:41.213 --> 18:44.137
But I saw bad people doing it.

18:44.377 --> 18:45.859
I'm really glad the youth on in this week.

18:45.919 --> 18:47.060
I was meant to do this last week.

18:47.101 --> 18:48.602
I'm really glad something that you threw out this week.

18:48.622 --> 18:50.585
So yeah, probably for the best.

18:52.728 --> 18:55.751
Testing reveals strengths and weaknesses.

18:56.753 --> 19:00.978
Things that maybe we thought we knew, but in fact we have still to learn.

19:01.634 --> 19:07.944
Temptation encourages us to cheat on the exam, to take a shortcut and do something that we know is wrong.

19:08.725 --> 19:15.956
And the notion of Israel, as they were hearing this, kind of the disciples hearing the shed, they would have understood this cycle of testing and temptation.

19:16.056 --> 19:23.468
And the Torah, so the first part of the Old Testament that they all would have known, carries these cycles of tests and temptation over and over again.

19:23.528 --> 19:25.311
And we'll know some of them fairly well.

19:25.731 --> 19:30.098
So right at the beginning, we see God places Adam and Eve in a garden.

19:30.274 --> 19:31.876
And it's a place of incredible blessing.

19:32.216 --> 19:35.920
And he says, you can eat from any tree except this one.

19:36.120 --> 19:38.122
Because if you eat from this tree, you'll die.

19:38.922 --> 19:46.129
And I don't know about you, but until I was writing this message, I'd never actually stopped to ask, why was there a tree in the first place?

19:46.150 --> 19:48.572
Why put the tree there to begin with?

19:48.672 --> 19:51.154
Surely it's just going to be a temptation.

19:52.115 --> 19:54.317
And I'm sure we can all empathize with that feeling.

19:55.158 --> 19:58.962
In a place of being told, you can have anything you want except that one thing

19:59.202 --> 20:00.945
that we all want that one thing, right?

20:01.025 --> 20:05.613
It's such a natural human thing to want the one thing that we're told that we can't have.

20:06.614 --> 20:15.890
But in choosing not to eat from the tree, they are constantly building their trust in God and in God's definition of good and evil rather than their own.

20:17.092 --> 20:23.282
And then we know the story as it goes, temptation comes in the form of a snake and twists God's words.

20:23.650 --> 20:33.185
And ultimately, it does what all temptation does, which is the only trick that temptation really has, which is to suggest that God is not good.

20:34.206 --> 20:38.253
Because if God is good, why wouldn't we trust Him?

20:39.635 --> 20:46.205
But if God isn't good, maybe if God's a liar, maybe He doesn't know what's best for us.

20:46.325 --> 20:48.048
Maybe He doesn't want what's best for us.

20:49.089 --> 20:52.114
Maybe we're better off doing things on our own.

20:52.866 --> 20:55.409
Well, then God is not to be trusted.

20:56.531 --> 21:01.277
And it is this lie from the serpent that says, did God really say?

21:02.819 --> 21:06.224
And then lies give way to doubts and mistrust.

21:07.165 --> 21:08.086
Did God really say?

21:08.126 --> 21:13.674
Did God really say not to eat from the fruit?

21:13.694 --> 21:17.038
And then they're empowered by their own desires and the need for control.

21:17.499 --> 21:19.161
And they choose not to follow God.

21:19.562 --> 21:22.706
And the blessing of Eden gives way to brokenness.

21:23.618 --> 21:33.889
but God is good, God restores them, and he clothes them, and he promises that one day a deliverer will come, and the cycle of testing and temptation begins again.

21:35.251 --> 21:37.673
And then a bit later, Abraham is tested by God.

21:38.234 --> 21:44.961
So trust me, God says, you will have a son in your older age, but decades go by and it hasn't happened.

21:45.562 --> 21:53.010
And Abraham and Sarah, doubting that God is really good, decide to take a shortcut and take matters into their own.

21:53.218 --> 21:55.781
hands, temptation comes.

21:57.203 --> 22:03.871
And temptation says that God isn't good, that he's broken his promise, that that thing that he said to you is gone.

22:04.812 --> 22:09.618
He can't be trusted, so you need to make things the way that you want them to be.

22:10.739 --> 22:20.311
And rather than wait for God to make good on his promise, Abraham has a baby with his wife, servant, Hagar, and it creates a pain and a division beyond what they can imagine.

22:21.753 --> 22:22.674
But even in that,

22:23.010 --> 22:24.853
church even in that God doesn't abandon them.

22:25.754 --> 22:35.408
He is still faithful and he still keeps his promises and Sarah does give birth to a son and God delivers and restores and the cycle begins again.

22:35.428 --> 22:46.705
Because tests from God are designed to lead us into growth and blessing but they are always twisted by the enemy into temptation.

22:48.187 --> 22:50.130
And it all comes back to that first lie

22:50.658 --> 22:57.386
that tells us in the moments that are hard, in the moments when we're struggling, that God is not good.

22:59.008 --> 23:04.215
Because if we believe God is good, then we know that we can trust Him to lead us.

23:05.416 --> 23:08.600
And we know that where He's led us, He won't abandon us.

23:09.922 --> 23:13.446
That He hasn't forgotten us, and He hasn't forgotten you.

23:15.208 --> 23:19.794
But then you might rightly ask if we're all talking about lead us not to dissemptation,

23:20.162 --> 23:21.984
Why pray against a good thing?

23:23.126 --> 23:33.338
If I'm standing up here telling you that God leads us into tests and tests build faith and that Satan is tempting us, why would we pray lead us not into temptation?

23:33.358 --> 23:37.744
Surely we would be yearning for God's testing to greater build our faith in him.

23:39.086 --> 23:40.027
Well, there's two problems with that.

23:40.688 --> 23:49.138
Firstly, anyone who's ever been tested knows that it's probably not something that we particularly yearn for or should particularly want.

23:49.282 --> 23:50.905
But let's think about it like this.

23:52.267 --> 23:56.313
So for those of you who've done it, you'll probably remember taking your driving test.

23:56.974 --> 24:00.259
And all the things you have to learn, you have to do things in a very specific way.

24:00.860 --> 24:02.723
And you have to really overdo it, don't you?

24:02.783 --> 24:04.346
Sit there and you go mirror.

24:06.829 --> 24:07.150
Signal.

24:07.170 --> 24:08.152
Forgot what you're trying to drive with.

24:08.572 --> 24:10.615
And then maneuver and go around.

24:10.635 --> 24:12.779
And you have to really overemphasize it.

24:12.899 --> 24:14.982
Now, we should all drive safely.

24:15.062 --> 24:17.426
And I'm sure you're all excellent drivers.

24:17.506 --> 24:20.210
But let's all be honest here for a second.

24:20.791 --> 24:30.327
If you have a driving license in the room, if you've taken a driving test and you have a driving license, I'd like you to stand up for me if that's OK, just for a moment, if you're able to.

24:30.347 --> 24:40.103
OK, now, if I took you outside to where the test center used to be and asked you to retake your driving test right now, if you think you'd still pass, stay standing.

24:40.123 --> 24:41.906
And if you think you'd fail, sit down.

24:44.770 --> 24:46.514
OK, I'm actually very impressed.

24:46.534 --> 24:49.722
Here we go, we have the safe drivers in the room are still standing and the unsafe driver.

24:49.762 --> 24:52.688
People you don't want to get a lift to church with are sitting down.

24:53.250 --> 24:56.317
Thanks very much everybody, you can sit down.

24:58.542 --> 25:03.634
I don't think I would pass my driving test if I took it today.

25:04.066 --> 25:05.328
And I asked this question once.

25:05.848 --> 25:08.692
I asked this question to a group of about 400 doctors and nurses.

25:08.832 --> 25:17.482
And I said, who here would pass your final exams that you took that allowed you to qualify to do what you do if you took it now?

25:17.803 --> 25:19.585
And every single person sat down.

25:19.645 --> 25:22.188
And it was a bit concerning.

25:23.650 --> 25:26.053
But it does make my point.

25:26.073 --> 25:29.117
Do I recognize that tests are important in my life?

25:29.617 --> 25:31.460
Driving tests, exams, and so on?

25:31.480 --> 25:33.522
Do I recognize that they serve a purpose?

25:33.698 --> 25:35.900
and that they are for my benefit, yes, of course I do.

25:36.941 --> 25:41.526
Do I believe that God's tests will help me grow in perseverance and help me grow spiritually?

25:41.666 --> 25:42.487
Yes, I do.

25:43.347 --> 25:47.491
Do I recognize that in life tests and temptations are inevitable?

25:48.032 --> 25:48.833
Yes, I do.

25:50.134 --> 26:02.386
But knowing what I know about myself and my current limitations and my own struggles with temptation, if I look inside my heart, would I really be wise to ask God to test me?

26:03.810 --> 26:12.863
Because this part of the Lord's prayer recognizes our own weakness, recognizes that we need humility in order to submit to God's will.

26:12.883 --> 26:15.226
Because the opposite of this would be saying, test me God.

26:15.587 --> 26:16.127
I've got this.

26:16.348 --> 26:17.149
Put me to the test.

26:17.409 --> 26:18.170
I'm going to nail it.

26:18.230 --> 26:18.771
Bring it on.

26:20.714 --> 26:22.316
And it would be very silly of me to do that.

26:24.199 --> 26:27.744
And we remember that Peter says to Jesus before Jesus has arrested.

26:28.785 --> 26:32.370
He says, even if all of these fall away from you, I never will.

26:32.802 --> 26:33.803
I'll never desert you.

26:34.664 --> 26:36.006
I will never deny you.

26:37.027 --> 26:38.469
And of course, we know exactly what happens.

26:39.090 --> 26:45.017
Peter denies Jesus three times just as Jesus predicted that he would and the rooster crows.

26:45.417 --> 26:48.721
And he realizes that he couldn't live up to what he said he was going to do.

26:50.523 --> 26:59.815
Lead us not into temptation brings us humbly before a God who loves us and says, God, I know, I know that I'm weaker than I think I am.

27:00.856 --> 27:02.578
If I can be spared testing,

27:03.010 --> 27:08.098
Please let me be spared, but ultimately lead me where you want me to go.

27:09.760 --> 27:25.323
Because even Jesus, even Jesus in the Garden of Gethsemane, knowing what was going to come, cried out to God, and he said, Father, if it is possible, let this cup be taken from me, but not my will, but yours.

27:28.728 --> 27:30.110
But so what?

27:30.130 --> 27:31.512
What can we take from this?

27:31.552 --> 27:32.754
How does this help us?

27:33.410 --> 27:35.372
Well, it helped me, I think, in a few ways.

27:36.654 --> 27:46.024
Firstly, I know that tests and trials are going to come, but I'm going to continue to pray, lead me not into temptation.

27:46.044 --> 27:48.667
God, anything I can be spared, please spare me.

27:49.508 --> 27:55.295
Anywhere I can avoid having to be tested and I can grow in other ways, please, please, please help me with that.

27:56.176 --> 27:58.258
Direct me away from everything

27:58.338 --> 28:04.909
that I don't absolutely have to go through and very much direct me away from problems and troubles and temptations of my own making.

28:06.531 --> 28:23.378
But if Jesus can pray to have these things taken away, then absolutely we can pray and cry out to God for healing, for restoration, for an end to the things that we're struggling with, for things to be easier, for battles to come to an end, absolutely we can pray for all of those things.

28:25.282 --> 28:33.172
But we know that those prayers aren't always answered, or at least not in the way or in the timeframe that we might want them to be or think that they should be.

28:34.333 --> 28:34.954
And that's hard.

28:35.955 --> 28:40.641
And I wish that I had an easy answer as to why it is that way.

28:41.201 --> 28:43.805
But I don't because sometimes it is just hard.

28:45.246 --> 28:54.898
But I do know that when I'm going through those things, that I can start to recognize the lie that has me question if God is still good.

28:55.586 --> 29:00.773
if he still loves me, if he still cares for me, if he still has my very best in mind.

29:03.216 --> 29:13.229
Because we can take heart from that and know that it's true and that anything that comes against that is a lie from the enemy that tries to draw me into temptation and to take shortcuts.

29:14.611 --> 29:22.802
I can be on my guard so that when the going gets tough and I'm tempted to do things my way, when I'm tempted to take a shortcut into sin,

29:23.330 --> 29:27.755
rather than trusting that my Heavenly Father is working for my best.

29:28.095 --> 29:30.398
And we all have moments like that.

29:30.418 --> 29:34.542
It's the moment where I've screwed up at work and I need to mess up.

29:34.562 --> 29:35.403
I need to say what I've done.

29:36.144 --> 29:38.006
But temptation says you could blame somebody else.

29:38.606 --> 29:39.247
You could hide it.

29:40.068 --> 29:40.589
No one knows.

29:42.090 --> 29:45.974
It's the moment where money is tight and I could cut corners.

29:46.675 --> 29:49.458
I could not declare payments in cash maybe.

29:49.954 --> 29:54.500
or maybe I just ignore God's call to be generous because it feels unsafe.

29:56.283 --> 30:11.263
It's the moment where I come home at the end of a stressful day, at the end of a stressful week, and no one's looking, and what I choose, or what I do, or what I consume, are they things that build me up, or are they things that tear me down?

30:12.424 --> 30:16.530
Because so often temptation is something that whispers to us when no one else is watching.

30:18.178 --> 30:21.321
And so forewarned here is forearmed.

30:22.082 --> 30:25.906
We can be on our guard against temptation when we know is coming.

30:26.006 --> 30:26.526
It is coming.

30:27.027 --> 30:36.596
And we know that Jesus has walked through temptation with us, and he will lead us through those temptations as well.

30:36.616 --> 30:39.899
But the reality is that we have all got this wrong at some point.

30:40.480 --> 30:41.461
We've all got this wrong somewhere.

30:41.521 --> 30:44.003
I've got this wrong in so many places.

30:44.844 --> 30:46.706
We've wandered off the path of following

30:46.882 --> 30:51.809
God at some point, and we've ended up, like we did in that car in Turkey, we've ended up in a big old ditch.

30:53.131 --> 30:55.335
But that doesn't mean that we have to stay there, praise God.

30:56.496 --> 31:00.542
Lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil.

31:01.504 --> 31:04.548
And that word deliver us, it has such power.

31:05.229 --> 31:09.916
And it's translated as well, it could be help us, rescue us, save us.

31:11.519 --> 31:16.306
And I think this petition, this cry out to God for help, is the ending of this prayer

31:16.610 --> 31:21.695
as Jesus teaches it, because it really does remind us of our dependence on God.

31:22.696 --> 31:36.749
Because if we finish the prayer with, give us our daily bread, or we forgive those who sin against us, we might be tempted to believe that somehow it's up to us, that we can handle life's trials and temptations on our own.

31:37.570 --> 31:42.034
So at Shul God, we've prayed that prayer, off we go, and we'll see you at the finish line.

31:43.695 --> 31:46.578
But instead, we're reminded that we absolutely can't do it.

31:46.850 --> 31:47.290
on our own.

31:48.452 --> 31:53.457
It's an acknowledgement that everything we've just prayed for up to this point that we're going to get wrong.

31:54.518 --> 31:55.299
That will fall short.

31:56.481 --> 32:03.628
But we know we don't have a God who abandons us but a God who rescues us and a God who delivers us.

32:04.950 --> 32:08.554
Because God isn't out there like some cosmic invigilator at an exam.

32:09.175 --> 32:15.922
He isn't setting up traps for us or being disappointed in our struggles or watching to see where we fall.

32:17.154 --> 32:18.335
He is our Father in heaven.

32:19.196 --> 32:20.318
He is the good shepherd.

32:20.818 --> 32:26.404
And time and time again, we see that when Israel faltered, God's promises still held.

32:27.305 --> 32:31.190
God did send Jesus to rescue us from what was lost in Eden.

32:31.250 --> 32:35.515
He did deliver the Israelites from slavery in Egypt to freedom in the promised land.

32:36.176 --> 32:39.139
Abraham and Sarah did have a son an old age.

32:39.800 --> 32:45.426
And whatever evil we have fallen into, he can and he will deliver us from as well.

32:46.146 --> 32:53.336
And I know this because there are so many stories of this right here in this room that we can hold on to because our God is always faithful.

32:54.678 --> 33:05.994
When my following goes astray, when I decide not to listen to his guidance, when I wander off and drive into a ditch, he comes right there to winch me out and rejoices that I am back.

33:07.275 --> 33:07.696
How do I know?

33:10.440 --> 33:14.866
Well, when Jesus told them this parable, suppose one of you has a hundred sheep

33:15.042 --> 33:16.264
and loses one of them.

33:17.165 --> 33:22.111
Doesn't he leave the 99 in the open country and go after the lost sheep until he finds it?

33:23.232 --> 33:27.458
And when he finds it, he joyfully puts it on his shoulders and goes home.

33:28.980 --> 33:35.167
Then he calls his friends and neighbours together and says, Rejoice with me for I have found my lost sheep.

33:37.470 --> 33:40.674
Church, when we fall in a ditch, the Lord pursues us.

33:41.455 --> 33:42.256
He's seeking us.

33:43.177 --> 33:43.698
He's not

33:44.002 --> 33:46.204
abandoned us in order to be with everybody else.

33:47.366 --> 33:47.886
He's there.

33:47.966 --> 33:51.210
He looks for us with everything else to pull us out.

33:54.514 --> 33:59.039
So maybe this morning you are in that place of feeling like you want to go your own way.

34:00.020 --> 34:00.660
Don't want to be led.

34:01.021 --> 34:03.303
Maybe there's a particular decision you don't want to be led in.

34:03.944 --> 34:06.487
Maybe it's just life in general.

34:06.507 --> 34:10.091
Can I encourage you that God isn't going to force you to be led by him?

34:10.912 --> 34:13.074
But whatever road we choose to go down,

34:13.378 --> 34:16.242
there will always be ditches and pitfalls.

34:17.664 --> 34:22.991
Can I encourage you that God is good and that he wants to lead you around those if you'll let him?

34:25.054 --> 34:28.078
Or maybe this morning you feel like you're somebody who's being tested.

34:29.180 --> 34:34.827
You're walking through something that's hard and the valley is getting darker and the walls feel like they're closing in.

34:36.069 --> 34:39.794
Can I encourage you to hold on to that truth that God is still good?

34:42.146 --> 34:52.677
If you feel like you have lost that truth in life and that the shortcuts are looking all the more tempting, that the good shepherd is still there leading you through.

34:55.140 --> 34:56.722
Or maybe you're in a ditch.

34:57.182 --> 34:58.323
Maybe you're in a ditch this morning.

34:58.343 --> 35:01.767
Maybe it's the kind of ditch that people warned you about and you've ended up there anyway.

35:02.848 --> 35:05.331
First of all, we've all been there at one time or another.

35:05.711 --> 35:07.793
You're not alone and you're not judged.

35:08.935 --> 35:12.018
But more importantly, your heavenly father is pursuing you.

35:12.898 --> 35:13.959
He wants to deliver you.

35:14.019 --> 35:15.161
He wants to rescue you.

35:15.221 --> 35:17.544
He wants to pull you out of that ditch.

35:18.064 --> 35:20.487
And it's not to school you or to touch at you.

35:20.507 --> 35:34.925
It's to rejoice with you because we are all sheep in the ditch and he can set us on the path of righteousness again, if we will allow ourselves to trust and come back to him.

35:36.446 --> 35:40.611
And so we pray lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil.

35:41.593 --> 35:42.834
We stand with me church as we pray.

35:48.834 --> 36:06.982
And in the moments where we haven't allowed you to lead us, and we've gone our own way, that you don't just abandon us, that you follow us, and that you are right there with us.

36:10.348 --> 36:16.978
And that I pray for wherever our hearts have been stubborn, wherever we have decided we want to go our own way,

36:17.090 --> 36:19.253
or wherever we've decided, actually, we don't want to turn around.

36:19.313 --> 36:22.178
We're stubbornly remaining in that ditch.

36:23.780 --> 36:26.884
Lord, I pray that Your hand would just come and reach out to each one of us this morning.

36:28.407 --> 36:30.149
Lord, that Your Spirit would guide us.

36:31.091 --> 36:32.993
That it would guide our hearts back to You.

36:33.915 --> 36:39.924
Lord, whether it's fear of condemnation or fear of rejection, we just push that aside in Jesus' name.

36:41.105 --> 36:44.210
We'll be thankful that You understand temptation, that You have lived

36:44.386 --> 36:49.855
temptation and that you overcame temptation, Lord.

36:49.875 --> 36:55.263
Let me take this moment to re-acknowledge your authority as king over our lives.

36:56.485 --> 37:02.635
A lot of me thank you that you are so, so good and that your promises endure forever.

37:03.596 --> 37:04.318
In your mighty name.

37:05.019 --> 37:05.219
Amen.

37:06.481 --> 37:07.122
Thanks, Judge.

